  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `Version: 1.10.6-stable`\r\nParameters: `ExecStart=/usr/bin/geth --rinkeby --http --http.corsdomain '*'  --http.addr 0.0.0.0 --http.api admin,db,eth,miner,web3,net,personal,txpool --ws --ws.addr 0.0.0.0 --ws.api admin,db,eth,miner,web3,net,personal,txpool --ws.origins '*' --datadir /mnt/volume_nyc1_04/ethereum --txpool.globalslots 75000 --txpool.accountslots 64 --txpool.accountqueue 16 --txpool.globalqueue 5000 --txpool.lifetime 24h0m0s --maxpeers 250`\r\nOS & Version: `Linux, Ubuntu Server 20.04 LTS`\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Explain the issue\r\nTransactions of type 2 (EIP1559) are broadcasted using the `web3.eth.subscribe('pendingTransactions'` event however they are \"dropped\" `getTransaction(hash)` returns null before they are confirmed. These transactions show in `rinkeby.etherscan.io` for awhile as pending before finally becoming marked as confirmed. Transaction for example of one that was dropped from our mempool but was confirmed. <https://rinkeby.etherscan.io/tx/0x3ecc9ff08ceb5b1e27a0ee637e8ddb886ab05548908cb77a4791639ee477d2b3>\r\n\r\nThis happens for every type 2 transaction.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nType 2 transactions should stay in the mempool until they are either confirmed as being dropped or included in a block. `getTransaction` shouldn't return `null` for valid transactions that the mempool was originally aware of.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nType 2 transactions are dropped from the mempool even when they're valid. \r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\nusing web3js..\r\n```js\r\nweb3.eth.subscribe('pendingTransactions', (error, result) => {})\r\n  .on('data', (hash) => {\r\n    let tx = web3.eth.getTransaction(hash);\r\n    console.log(tx != null); // true \r\n    setTimeout(() => {\r\n      tx = web3.eth.getTransaction(hash);\r\n      console.log(tx != null); // false\r\n      // This transaction will still confirm. \r\n    }, 500);\r\n  });\r\n```\r\n\r\nWe don't run into this issue with any legacy transactions. We keep a database of transactions and associated data and remove them as they're dropped from the mempool. ",
